OLS

\[ \begin{aligned} y_t &= \beta_0 + \beta_1 x_t + \epsilon_t,\\[1em] &\quad \text{or}\\[1em] y &= X \begin{bmatrix}\beta_0 \\ \beta_1 \end{bmatrix} + \epsilon,\\[1em] &\epsilon \sim N(0, \sigma^2I_N) \end{aligned} \]

\[ y, X \]

\[ \beta, \sigma^2 \]

3

\(\epsilon \sim N(0, \sigma^2I_N)\)\(\{y,X\}\)\(\{\beta, \sigma\}\)joint distribution \[ \begin{aligned} p(y|\beta, \sigma^2) &= \prod_{n=1}^N \left[ \frac{1}{\sqrt{2\pi }\sigma} \exp \left( -\frac{1}{2\sigma^2}\epsilon_n^2 \right) \right]\\ &= \prod_{n=1}^N \left[ \frac{1}{\sqrt{2\pi }\sigma} \exp \left( -\frac{1}{2\sigma^2}(y_n-X_n \beta)^2 \right) \right]\\ &= \left( \frac{1}{\sqrt{2\pi }\sigma} \right)^N \exp \left[-\frac{1}{2\sigma^2}\sum_{n=1}^{N} (y_n-X_n \beta)^2 \right] \\ &= \left( \frac{1}{2\pi\sigma^2} \right)^{N/2} \exp \left[ -\frac{1}{2\sigma^2}(y-X\beta)'(y-X\beta) \right]. \end{aligned} \] \(h\) \[ p(y|\beta, h)= \left( \frac{h}{2\pi} \right)^{N/2} \exp \left[ -\frac{h}{2}(y-X\beta)'(y-X\beta) \right] \quad \text{(Koop 3.3)}. \]

OLS \[ \begin{alignat}{2} \hat{\beta}&=(X'X)^{-1}X'y\\ SSE &= (y - X\hat{\beta})'(y - X\hat{\beta})\\ \hat{\nu} &= N-k && \quad \text{(Koop 3.4)}\\ \hat{s}^2 &= \frac{SSE}{\nu} \end{alignat} \] \[ (y-X\beta)'(y-X\beta)=SSE+(\beta-\hat{\beta})'X'X(\beta-\hat{\beta})=\hat{\nu}\hat{s}^2+(\beta-\hat{\beta})'X'X(\beta-\hat{\beta}) \] \[ \boxed{\begin{alignedat}{2} p(y|\beta, h)&= \left( \frac{h}{2\pi} \right)^{N/2} \exp \left[ -\frac{h}{2}\left\{ \underbrace{ \hat{\nu}\hat{s}^2 }_{=SSE}+(\beta-\hat{\beta})'X'X(\beta-\hat{\beta}) \right\} \right] &&\quad \text{(BEM 10.4)}, \\ \text{or}\\ p(y|\beta, h)&= \left( \frac{1}{2\pi} \right)^{N/2} \underbrace{ \left\{h^\frac{k}{2} \exp \left[ -\frac{h}{2}(\beta-\hat{\beta})'X'X(\beta-\hat{\beta}) \right]\right\} }_{\text{(Normal)}} \underbrace{ \left\{h^\frac{\nu}{2} \exp \left[ -\frac{h\nu}{2\hat{s}^{-2}} \right]\right\} }_{\text{(Gamma)}} &&\quad \text{(Koop 3.7)} \end{alignedat}} \]

\(\{\beta, h\}\)priorNormal-GammaNormal-Gamma(def)Hyperparameter

4.1 Gamma

Gamma\(\alpha\)\(\beta\) \[ \begin{aligned} & p(h; \alpha, \beta) ={C_G}^{-1} h^{\alpha - 1} \cdot e^\frac{-h}{\beta},\\ &\, \text{where }{C_G} = \beta^\alpha\Gamma(\alpha) \end{aligned} \]

\(h\)\(\underline{s}\)\(\underline{\nu}\)GammaGamma \[ \alpha = {\underline{\nu}}/{2}, \, \beta = {2\underline{s}^{-2}}/{\underline{\nu}} \] \[ p(h; \underline{s}, \underline{\nu}) ={C_\gamma}^{-1} h^{\underline{\nu}-2/2} \cdot \exp\left[-\frac{1}{2} h \frac{\underline{\nu}}{\underline{s}^{-2}}\right] \] \[ \begin{aligned} \mathbb{E}[h] &= \alpha \beta = \frac{\underline{\nu}}{2}\frac{2\underline{s}^{-2}}{\underline{\nu}} = \underline{s}^{-2}\\ \text{Var}[h] &= \alpha \beta^2 = \frac{\underline{\nu}}{2}\left(\frac{2\underline{s}^{-2}}{\nu}\right)^2 = \frac{2\underline{s}^{-4}}{\underline{\nu}} \end{aligned}\] \(\underline{s}\)\(h\)\(\underline{\nu}\)

4.2

\(\)\(N(\overline{\mathbf{\beta}}, h^{-1}\overline{\mathbf{Q}})\) \[ \begin{aligned} p(\beta|h; \underline{\beta}, \underline{Q}) &= \frac{1}{2\pi^{\frac{1}{2}k}}|h^{-1}\underline{Q}|^{-\frac{1}{2}}\exp\left[ -\frac{1}{2}(\beta-\underline{\beta})'[h^{-1}\underline{Q}]^{-1}(\beta-\underline{\beta}) \right]\\ &= \frac{1}{2\pi^{\frac{1}{2}k}}\underbrace{ (h^{-k}|\underline{Q}|) }_{\text{}}^{-\frac{1}{2}}\exp\left[ -\frac{h}{2}(\beta-\underline{\beta})'\underline{Q}^{-1}(\beta-\underline{\beta}) \right]\\ &= \left( \frac{h}{2\pi} \right)^{\frac{1}{2}k} |\underline{Q}|^{-\frac{1}{2}}\exp\left[ -\frac{h}{2}(\beta-\underline{\beta})'\underline{Q}^{-1}(\beta-\underline{\beta}) \right] \end{aligned} \]

5

\[ \boxed{\begin{alignedat}{3} p(y|\beta, h)&= \left( \frac{h}{2\pi} \right)^{N/2} \exp \left[ -\frac{h}{2}\left\{ \nu \hat{s}^2 +(\beta-\hat{\beta})'X'X(\beta-\hat{\beta}) \right\} \right] && \quad \dots \text{}\\ p(h; \underline{s}, \underline{\nu}) &={C_\gamma}^{-1} h^{\underline{\nu}-2/2} \cdot \exp\left[-\frac{1}{2} h \frac{\underline{\nu}}{\underline{s}^{-2}}\right] && \quad \dots \text{Gamma}\\ p(\beta|h,\underline{\beta}, \underline{Q}) &=\left( \frac{h}{2\pi} \right)^{k/2} |\underline{Q}|^{-\frac{1}{2}}\exp\left[ -\frac{h}{2}(\beta-\underline{\beta})'\underline{Q}^{-1}(\beta-\underline{\beta}) \right] && \quad \dots \text{} \end{alignedat}} \]

5.1

\[ \begin{aligned} p(\beta, h |y) &\propto \underbrace{p(\beta, h; \underline{\beta},\underline{Q}, \underline{s}, \underline{\nu})}_{\text{ HPparameter}} \times \underbrace{ p(y|\beta, h) }_\text{parameter}\\ &= \quad p(\beta | h; \underline{\beta},\underline{Q})p(h; \underline{s}, \underline{\nu}) \quad \times \quad p(y|\beta, h)\\[1em] \Rightarrow \,p(\beta, h |y) &\propto \left( \frac{h}{2\pi} \right)^{k/2} |\underline{Q}|^{-\frac{1}{2}}\exp\left[ -\frac{h}{2}(\beta-\underline{\beta})'\underline{Q}^{-1}(\beta-\underline{\beta}) \right]\quad\dots\text{}\\ &\quad \quad \times {C_\gamma}^{-1} h^{(\underline{\nu}-2)/2} \cdot \exp\left[-\frac{h}{2} \frac{\underline{\nu}}{\underline{s}^{-2}}\right] \quad\dots\text{Gamma}\\ &\quad \quad \times \left( \frac{h}{2\pi} \right)^{N/2} \exp \left[ -\frac{h}{2}\left\{ \hat{\nu} \hat{s}^2 +(\beta-\hat{\beta})'X'X(\beta-\hat{\beta}) \right\} \right] \quad\dots\text{}\\ & \propto h^{\frac{k+\underline{\nu}-2+N}{2}} \exp \left[ -\frac{h}{2} \left\{\underline{\nu}\underline{s}^{2}+\hat{\nu} \hat{s}^2+(\beta-\underline{\beta})'\underline{Q}^{-1}(\beta-\underline{\beta})+(\beta-\hat{\beta})'X'X(\beta-\hat{\beta})\right\} \right]. \end{aligned} \] \((\beta-\underline{\beta})'\underline{Q}^{-1}(\beta-\underline{\beta})+(\beta-\hat{\beta})'X'X(\beta-\hat{\beta})\)

  • \((\beta-\underline{\beta})'\underline{Q}^{-1}(\beta-\underline{\beta})\): \(\beta\)prior\(\underline\beta\)
  • \((\beta-\hat{\beta})'X'X(\beta-\hat{\beta})\):\(\beta\)\(\hat\beta\)

\[ \begin{aligned} &(\beta-\underline{\beta})'\underline{Q}^{-1}(\beta-\underline{\beta})+(\beta-\hat{\beta})'X'X(\beta-\hat{\beta})\\ =& (\beta-\bar{\beta})'\bar{Q}^{-1}(\beta-\bar{\beta}) +\underbrace{ (\underline{\beta}-\bar{\beta})'\underline{Q}^{-1}(\underline{\beta}-\bar{\beta}) +(\hat{\beta}-\bar{\beta})'X'X(\hat{\beta}-\bar{\beta}) }_{\beta\text{$h$}}\\ =& (\beta-\bar{\beta})'\bar{Q}^{-1}(\beta-\bar{\beta}) +(\underline{\beta}-\hat{\beta})'[{\underline{Q}+(X'X)^{-1}}]^{-1}(\underline{\beta}-\hat{\beta}) \end{aligned} \] \[ \boxed{\begin{aligned} p(\beta,h\mid y) \propto h^{\frac{k+\bar{\nu}-2}{2}} \exp\Bigg[ -\frac{h}{2}\Big\{ &\underline{\nu}\underline{s}^{2}+ \hat{\nu}\hat{s}^2 +(\beta-\bar{\beta})'\bar{Q}^{-1}(\beta-\bar{\beta})\\ & +(\underline{\beta}-\hat{\beta})'[{\underline{Q}+(X'X)^{-1}}]^{-1}(\underline{\beta}-\hat{\beta}) \Big\} \Bigg],\\ \text{or}\\ p(\beta,h\mid y) \propto h^{\frac{k+\bar{\nu}-2}{2}} \exp\Bigg[ -\frac{h}{2}\Big\{ &(\beta-\bar{\beta})'\bar{Q}^{-1}(\beta-\bar{\beta})+\bar{\nu} \bar{s}^2 \Big\} \Bigg]. \end{aligned}} \] \[ \boxed{\therefore \beta, h | y \sim NG(\bar{\beta}, \bar{Q}, \bar{s}^{-2}, \bar{\nu})} \] \[ \begin{alignedat}{2} \bar{Q} &= (\underline{Q}^{-1}+X'X)^{-1},&&\quad \text{(Koop 3.10)}\\ \bar{\beta} &= \bar{Q}(\underline{Q}^{-1}\underline{\beta}+X'X\hat{\beta}), &&\quad \text{(Koop 3.11)}\\ \bar{\nu} &= \underline{\nu}+N, &&\quad \text{(Koop 3.12)}\\ \bar{\nu}\bar{s}^2 &= \underline{\nu}\underline{s}^2+\hat{\nu}\hat{s}^2+(\underline{\beta}-\hat{\beta})'[{\underline{Q}+(X'X)^{-1}}]^{-1}(\underline{\beta}-\hat{\beta}), &&\quad \text{(Koop 3.13)}\\ \end{alignedat} \]

5.2 \(\beta\)

\(p(\beta,h|y)\)\(h\)\(\beta\)\(\exp \{\,\}\)1 \[ p(\beta, h|y)\propto \exp \left[-\frac{1}{2}(\beta-\bar{\beta})'[h^{-1}\bar{Q}]^{-1}(\beta-\bar{\beta})\right]. \] \[ \boxed{ \begin{aligned}\beta|h,y \sim N(\bar{\beta},h^{-1}\bar{Q}),\end{aligned}\\[1em] \left.\begin{aligned}\bar{Q} &= (\underline{Q}^{-1}+X'X)^{-1},\\ \bar{\beta} &= \bar{Q}(\underline{Q}^{-1}\underline{\beta}+X'X\hat{\beta}) \end{aligned}\right\} \quad (\text{})} \]

Interpretation: - OLS\(\bar{\beta} \underline{\beta}\)\((X'X)^{-1} \underline{Q}\).

\[ \text{OLS:} \quad \text{Var}[b|X] = \sigma^2(X'X)^{-1} \tag{Greene 4-15} \]

  • \(\bar{\beta}\)prior\(\underline{\beta}\)\(\hat{\beta}\)\(\underline{Q}\)prior;\(X'X\)

5.3 \(h\)

\(h\)\(\beta\) \[ p(h|y) = \int p(\beta,h|y) d\beta \] \(p(\beta,h|y)\)\(\beta\)\(\exp\)1 \[ \begin{aligned} p(h|y) &\propto \int p(\beta,h|y) d\beta\\ &= h^{\frac{k+\underline{\nu}-2+N}{2}} \exp\left[-\frac{h}{2}\bar{\nu}\bar{s}^2\right] \int \exp \left[ -\frac{1}{2} (\beta-\bar{\beta})'h\bar{Q}^{-1}(\beta-\bar{\beta})\right]d\beta. \end{aligned} \]

Integral \[ \int \exp \left[-\frac{1}{2} (\beta-\bar{\beta})'h\bar{Q}^{-1}(\beta-\bar{\beta})\right] d\beta=(2\pi)^{k/2}|h\bar{Q}^{-1}|^{-1/2}=(2\pi)^{k/2}h^{-k/2}|\bar{Q}^{-1}|^{-1/2} \] \[ \begin{aligned} p(h\mid y) &\propto h^{\frac{k+\bar{\nu}-2}{2}} \exp\left[-\frac{h}{2}\bar{\nu}\bar{s}^2\right] (2\pi)^{k/2}h^{-k/2}|\bar{Q}^{-1}|^{-1/2}\\ &= h^{\frac{\bar{\nu}-2}{2}}\exp\left[-\frac{h}{2}\bar{\nu}\bar{s}^2\right] (2\pi)^{k/2}|\bar{Q}|^{1/2}\\ &\propto h^{\frac{\bar{\nu}-2}{2}}\exp\left[-\frac{h}{2}\bar{\nu}\bar{s}^2\right] \end{aligned} \]

\[ \beta, h|y \sim NG(\bar{\beta}, \bar{Q}, \bar{s},\bar{\nu}), \]

calculate_bayesian_analytical_solution <- function(y, X, beta_prior, Q_prior, nu_prior, s2_prior) {
  n <- nrow(X)  # Number of observations
  XTX <- t(X) %*% X
  XTy <- t(X) %*% y
  Q_posterior <- XTX + Q_prior
  beta_posterior <- solve(Q_posterior, XTy + Q_prior %*% beta_prior)
  nu_posterior <- nu_prior + n

  term1 <- nu_prior * s2_prior
  term2 <- t(y) %*% y
  term3 <- t(beta_prior) %*% Q_prior %*% beta_prior
  term4 <- t(beta_posterior) %*% Q_posterior %*% beta_posterior

  nu_s2_posterior_sum <- term1 + term2 + term3 - term4
  s2_posterior <- as.numeric(nu_s2_posterior_sum[1, 1] / nu_posterior)

  list(
    beta_posterior = beta_posterior,
    Q_posterior    = Q_posterior,
    nu_posterior   = nu_posterior,
    s2_posterior   = s2_posterior
  )
}

### 
calculate_likelihood <- function(beta, h, y, X) {
  N <- length(y)
  constant_part <- (h / (2 * pi))^(N / 2) # (h/2pi)^(N/2)
  residual <- y - X %*% beta
  sse <- t(residual) %*% residual
  exponential_part <- exp(- h/2 * sse)
  as.numeric(constant_part * exponential_part)
}

6.3 Gamma

\[ \begin{aligned} \underline{\beta} &= \begin{pmatrix}0.0\\0.0\end{pmatrix},\\ \underline{Q} &= \begin{bmatrix}1 & 0\\ 0 & 1\end{bmatrix},\\ \underline{\nu} &= \quad 2.0,\\ \underline{s}^2 &= \quad 0.5. \end{aligned} \]

# 3.  (Informative Prior: Normal-Gamma)
beta_prior <- matrix(c(0.0, 0.0), ncol = 1) # : beta = [0, 0]'
Q_prior <- diag(k) * 1.0                   #  Q (): Q = diag(1, 1)
nu_prior <- 2.0                            # /
s2_prior <- 0.5                            #  E[sigma^2] = 0.5 -> E[h] = 2
calculate_h_prior_kernel <- function(h_param, nu, s2) {
  alpha <- nu / 2.0
  beta  <- (nu * s2) / 2.0
  if (h_param <= 0) return(0.0)
  (h_param^(alpha - 1)) * exp(-beta * h_param)
}
h_range <- seq(0.1, 10.0, length.out = 50)

# 
kernel_values_h <- numeric(length(h_range))

for (i in seq_along(h_range)) {
  h_point <- h_range[i]
  kernel_values_h[i] <- calculate_h_prior_kernel(h_point, nu_prior, s2_prior)
}

# 
plot(h_range, kernel_values_h, type = "l",
     xlab = "h (Precision)", ylab = "Kernel Value",
     main = "Prior Kernel for Precision h (nu_prior, s2_prior)")
grid()

6.4 

calculate_conditional_posterior_beta_kernel <- function(beta, beta_bar, h, Q_bar) {
  k <- length(beta)
  deviation <- beta - beta_bar
  quadratic_form <- t(deviation) %*% Q_bar %*% deviation
  as.numeric((h^(k/2)) * exp(-0.5 * h * quadratic_form[1,1]))
}

    grid_df$likelihood[r] <- calculate_likelihood(beta_vector, h_val, y, X)

  }

  }

6.7 Gibbs Sampling

\[ \boxed{p(\beta,h\mid y) \propto h^{\frac{k+\bar{\nu}-2}{2}} \exp\Bigg[ -\frac{h}{2}\Big\{ (\beta-\bar{\beta})'\bar{Q}^{-1}(\beta-\bar{\beta})+\bar{\nu} \bar{s}^2 \Big\} \Bigg]\quad \text{}} \]

\(\{\dot{\beta},\dot{Q},\dot{\nu},\dot{s}\}\)

\(\beta\)

\[ \boxed{\beta|h \sim N(\dot{\beta},h^{-1}\dot Q),} \] \[ \text{where}\quad \begin{aligned} \dot{Q} &= \bar{Q} = (\underline{Q}^{-1}+X'X)^{-1},\\ \dot{\beta} &= \bar{\beta}= \bar{Q}(\underline{Q}^{-1}\underline{\beta}+X'X\hat{\beta}). \end{aligned} \]

\(h\)\(\beta\)Gamma:

\[ \boxed{h|\beta \sim \gamma(\dot{s}^{-2},\dot{\nu}),} \]

\[ \begin{aligned} \dot{\nu}&=\underbrace{\bar{\nu}}_{\underline{\nu}+N}+k,\\ \dot{\nu}\dot{s}^2 &= \underbrace{\bar{\nu}\bar{s}^2}_{ \underline{\nu}\underline{s}^{2}+\hat{\nu} \hat{s}^2+(\underline{\beta}-\bar{\beta})'\underline{Q}^{-1}(\underline{\beta}-\bar{\beta}) }+({\beta}-\bar{\beta})'\dot{Q}^{-1}({\beta}-\bar{\beta}). \end{aligned} \]

\(\dot{\nu}\dot{s}^2\)\(h\)marginal posterior \(\bar{\nu} \bar{s}^2\) \(\beta\)\(({\beta}-\bar{\beta})'\bar{Q}^{-1}({\beta}-\bar{\beta})\)

  • Step 12 \(S\) \(\{(\beta^{(s)}, h^{(s)})\}\) \(p(\beta,h|y)\)

6.7.0.2

Gibbs sampler

# Gibbs sampler as a function (NormalGamma regression posterior)
#   beta | h, y  ~ N(beta_bar, h^{-1} Q_bar)
#   h | beta, y  ~ Gamma(shape = (nu_bar + k)/2,
#                        rate  = (nu_bar*s2_bar + (beta-beta_bar)'Q_bar^{-1}(beta-beta_bar))/2)

gibbs_ng <- function(beta_bar, Q_bar, nu_bar, s2_bar,
                     h_init = 1.0, n_samples = 1000, seed = NULL) {
  if (!is.null(seed)) set.seed(seed)

  k <- nrow(beta_bar)
  Qbar_inv <- solve(Q_bar)
  
  # variables to store the results
  beta1 <- numeric(n_samples)
  h_draw <- numeric(n_samples)
  
  ### initial h ###
  current_h <- h_init
  
  ### Gibbs iteration ###
  for (s in seq_len(n_samples)) {
    ### Step 1: draw beta | h, y ###
    cov_beta <- Q_bar / current_h  # (h^{-1} Q_bar)
    b <- MASS::mvrnorm(n = 1, mu = as.numeric(beta_bar), Sigma = cov_beta)
    
    # update b -> store beta1 (2nd element)
    b <- matrix(b, ncol = 1)
    beta1[s] <- b[2, 1]

    ### Step 2: draw h | beta, y  ###
    quad <- as.numeric(t(b - beta_bar) %*% Qbar_inv %*% (b - beta_bar))  # scalar
    shape_h <- (nu_bar + k) / 2
    rate_h  <- (nu_bar * s2_bar + quad) / 2
    
    # update h -> store 
    current_h <- rgamma(1, shape = shape_h, rate = rate_h)
    h_draw[s] <- current_h
  }
  
  # return
  data.frame(
    iter   = seq_len(n_samples),
    beta1  = beta1,
    h      = h_draw,
    h_init = h_init
  )
}

\(h^{(0)}=(1, 10000, 0.001)\)3

  • \(h\)\(\beta^{(1)}\)

  • \(h\)posterior mean\(\bar \beta\)\(\beta^{(1)}\)

h_inits <- c(1, 10000, 0.001)
